# Codebase exploration in mcp-adjutant

**Overrides the global `fastcontext.mdc` rule in this workspace.**

This repo *is* mcp-adjutant. When the `mcp-adjutant` MCP server is connected, follow [`.cursor/skills/mcp-adjutant-delegation/SKILL.md`](../skills/mcp-adjutant-delegation/SKILL.md) at **hard** level (`MCP_ADJUTANT_DELEGATION_LEVEL=hard`).

## MCP-first — use adjutant before native tools

When adjutant MCP tools are available, **do not** substitute native tools for matching work:

| Task | MCP tool | Do NOT use instead |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Log investigation, crash/CI log triage | `analyze_log` | Grep, Read, fastcontext on log files |
| Repo context, tracing, impact analysis | `scout_context` | fastcontext, Grep chains, Task explore |
| After code changes | `verify_and_triage` | manual cargo/npm, ReadLints only |
| Tests for new/changed `src/` logic | `generate_tests_and_scaffolding` | hand-written test files |
| External docs, API specs, library behavior | `web_fetch` | WebSearch, WebFetch |
| Rename/signature across files | `execute_global_refactor` | manual multi-file edits |
| Every sub-agent result before use | `evaluate_agent_performance` | trusting output unchecked |

Poll `query_job_status` until `terminal=true` for every async tool. Read the delegation skill for retry/evaluator loops and the session checklist.

When `MCP_ADJUTANT_REQUIRE_BUILDER=true`, skipping builder after `src/` edits is a rule violation.
When `MCP_ADJUTANT_REQUIRE_LOG_ANALYZER=true`, skipping `analyze_log` when a task touches log files is a rule violation.

## When FastContext CLI is allowed (fallback only)

Use `fastcontext -q "<question; file:line evidence>" --max-turns 8` only when:

- mcp-adjutant MCP is **not** connected, or
- `scout_context` failed after skill-appropriate retries, or
- **Single obvious file** / trivial symbol lookup (`rg` / `Read` is fine too)

Endpoint: `http://127.0.0.1:8080/v1`, model `fastcontext`, 32k context.
If down: `launchctl kickstart -k gui/$(id -u)/com.andrzej.fastcontext.llama-server`.

FastContext remains read-only evidence gathering — never a substitute for adjutant scout, triage, builder, web_fetch, or evaluation when MCP is up.
